# Project Name

This is a server backend services that fetches a pokemon API services end point and however returned to the user.

## Getting Started

Follow these steps to set up and run the project on your local machine.

### Prerequisites

Before you begin, make sure you have the following installed:

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (version latest)
- [npm](https://www.npmjs.com/) (version latest or [Yarn](https://yarnpkg.com/) (version x.x.x)
- [TypeScript](https://www.typescriptlang.org/) (version latest)

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:

    ```sh
    git clone https://github.com/tohshine/homeOfficeInterview
    cd your-project
    ```

2. Install dependencies:

    ```sh
    npm install
    # or
    yarn install
    ```

## Usage

To build and start the application, follow these steps:
1. Add .env the root direction has describe in the .env.example by adding the BASE_URL with the pokemon url

2. Build the production code:

    ```sh
    npm run prod:server
    # or
    yarn prod:server
    ```
3. start the optimized production code :

    ```sh
    npm start
    # or
    yarn start
    ```    
4. start and run the test suit jest  :

    ```sh
    npm run test
    # or
    yarn run test
    ```     

5. Start the application in development:

    ```sh
    npm dev:server
    # or
    yarn dev:server
    ```
5. Using Postman  to access the route:
   - open your post man change the request method to post  with url of /api/pokemon
   - with with pokemonName of {pokemon:"butterfree"}
   - the request body returns a structured data with list of pokemon and its variations
       

The application should now be running and accessible at [http://localhost:5000](http://localhost:5000).

## Contributing

If you'd like to contribute to this project, please follow these steps:

1. Fork this repository.
2. Create a new branch for your feature or bug fix:

    ```sh
    git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name
    ```

3. Make your changes and commit them.
4. Push your changes to your fork:

    ```sh
    git push origin feature/your-feature-name
    ```

5. Create a pull request against the `main` branch of this repository.

